{{EngvarB|date=April 2017}} {{Use dmy dates|date=April 2017}} {{Infobox film awards | number = 15 | award = Meril Prothom Alo Awards | image = | caption = | date = 26 April 2013 | site = Hall of Fame Theatre, [[Bangabandhu International Conference Center]], [[Dhaka]], Bangladesh | host = [[Rumana Malik Munmun]], [[Mosharraf Karim]], & [[Chanchal Chowdhury]] | preshow= [[Rumana Malik Munmun]] | producer = [[Transcom Group]], [[Square Toiletries]] | director = Kabir Bakul | network = Maasranga Television | best_picture = ''[[Ghetuputra Komola]]'' | most_wins = ''[[Ghetuputra Komola]]'' (5) | most_nominations = ''[[Ghetuputra Komola]]'' (5) | duration = 1 hours, 12 minutes | ratings = | last = 14th | next = 16th }} The '''15th Meril Prothom Alo Awards''' ceremony, presented by Prothom Alo took place on 26 April 2013, at the [[Bangabandhu International Conference Center]] in Dhaka, Bangladesh as a part of the 2012–13 film awards season.
==Facts and figures== This was 15th instalment of Meril Prothom Alo Awards. ''[[Ghetuputra Komola]]'' got the best film awards along with 4 other awards of Critics Choice best director, best film actor, best film actress, and a special award. This was the last directed film of popular novelist [[Humayun Ahmed]]. He was awarded as the best film director for this film. [[Nazmun Munira Nancy]] got the award in best female singer category for the fourth time in a row from 2009.
==Winners and nominations== A total of 14 awards were given at the ceremony. Following is the list of the winners.
===Lifetime Achievement Award – 2013=== * Prominent singer [[Ramkanai Das]]<ref>{{cite news |author=Zahangir Alom |date=7 September 2014 |title=Sunset of a Music Maestro |url=http://www.thedailystar.net/sunset-of-a-music-maestro-40468 |newspaper=[[The Daily Star (Bangladesh)|The Daily Star]]}}</ref>
