{{Infobox album | name = Hidden Stash 420 | type = compilation | artist = [[Kottonmouth Kings]] | cover = Hidden Stash 420 cover.jpg | alt = | released = October 13, 2009 | recorded = | venue = | studio = | genre = [[Hip hop music|Hip hop]], [[rap rock]], [[rapcore]], [[alternative metal]] | length = 2:34:51 | label = [[Suburban Noize Records|Suburban Noize]] | producer = [[Daddy X]] and Kevin Zinger | prev_title = [[The Green Album (Kottonmouth Kings album)|The Green Album]] | prev_year = 2008 | next_title = [[Long Live The Kings]] | next_year = 2010 }} {{Album ratings |rev1 = [[Allmusic]] |rev1score = {{Rating|3|5}}<ref name="AMG">[{{Allmusic|class=album|id=r1646666|pure_url=yes}} Allmusic review]</ref> |rev2 = RapReviews |rev2score = (7/10)<ref name="RapReviews">[http://www.rapreviews.com/archive/2009_12_hiddenstash420.html RapReviews review]</ref> }}<!-- Automatically generated by DASHBot-->
'''''Hidden Stash 420''''' is a 2009 compilation album from American [[hip hop]] group [[Kottonmouth Kings]]. It is their fourth compilation album and includes b-sides, remixes, demos, solo tracks by Kottonmouth Kings members [[D-Loc]] and [[Johnny Richter]], and collaborations with other artists. The album comprises 40 tracks on two discs.<ref name="AMG"/>
The [[Best Buy]] edition of the album includes a bonus DVD titled ''Lost Adventures'' which consists of two hours of behind the scenes footage and videos.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.myspace.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=blog.ListAll&friendId=63447058 |title=Kottonmouth Kings &#124; blog op Myspace |publisher=Blogs.myspace.com |date= |accessdate=2012-02-21 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091114225132/http://blogs.myspace.com/index.cfm?fuseaction=blog.ListAll&friendId=63447058 |archivedate=2009-11-14 |df= }}</ref>
