'''''How Did This Get Made?''''' (HDTGM) is a [[podcast]] on the [[Earwolf]] network. It is hosted by [[Paul Scheer]], [[June Diane Raphael]] and [[Jason Mantzoukas]]. Each show, which typically has a different guest, features the deconstruction and mockery of outlandish and [[List of films considered the worst|bad films]].

==Format==
The hosts and guest make jokes about the films as well as attempt to unscramble plots. After discussing the film, Scheer reads "second opinions" in the form of five-star reviews posted online by [[Amazon.com]] users. The hosts also often make recommendations on if the film is worth watching. The show is released every two weeks. During the show's off week a ".5" episode (also known as a "minisode") is uploaded featuring Scheer announcing the next week's movie as well as challenges for the fans. Some full episodes are recorded in front of a live audience and include a question and answer session.<ref name="avc213">{{cite web |url=http://www.avclub.com/article/paul-scheer-picks-his-favorite-ihow-did-this-get-m-92111 | title=Paul Scheer picks his favorite How Did This Get Made? episodes | work=A.V. Club | date=February 7, 2013 | accessdate=July 26, 2014 | author=Rabin, Nathan}}</ref><ref name="earwolf-hdtgm">{{cite web |url=http://www.earwolf.com/show/how-did-this-get-made/ | title=How Did This Get Made? | publisher=Earwolf | accessdate=July 26, 2014}}</ref><ref name="recom714">{{cite web |url=http://www.rogerebert.com/interviews/interview-paul-scheer-of-how-did-this-get-made | title=Interview: Paul Scheer of "How Did This Get Made?" | publisher=RogerEbert.com | date=July 22, 2014 | accessdate=July 26, 2014 | author=Lindsey, Craig D.}}</ref>

==History==
The podcast was started when the hosts were talking about how bad ''[[Wall Street: Money Never Sleeps]]'' was over drinks and after seeing ''[[Old Dogs (film)|Old Dogs]]'' in the theater.<ref name="avc213" /><ref name="earwolf-hdtgm" /><ref name="recom714" />

==''Unspooled''==
In May 2018, Paul began a new podcast also devoted to movies, called ''[[Unspooled]]'', but this time those deemed good enough for the AFI Top 100. This is often referenced in ''How Did This Get Made'', often by Jason and June, annoyed at how they hadn't been invited to host this new podcast, instead being subjected to the bad films that HDTGM cover.

==Episode guide==
The show is released every two weeks. During the show's off week, a ".5" episode is uploaded featuring Scheer announcing the next week's movie as well as challenges for the fans.<ref name="avc213" /><ref name="earwolf-hdtgm" /> In addition to the shows and mini-shows, the ''How Did This Get Made?'' stream hosted the first three episodes of [[Casey Wilson]] and [[Danielle Schneider]]'s ''Bitch Sesh'' podcast in December 2015. It has hosted episodes of its own spin-off podcast ''How Did This Get Made? Origin Stories'' in which Blake Harris interviews people involved with the films covered by the main show. In December 2017, an episode was recorded for the Pee Cast Blast event, and released exclusively on Stitcher Premium.
