{{Refimprove|date=January 2017}} {{Infobox company | name = Mediaset Premium | logo = | type = Pay TV | foundation = 20 January 2005 | location_city = [[Milan]], [[Italy]] | key_people = | products = | industry = [[Pay television]] | homepage = [http://www.mediasetpremium.it/ mediasetpremium.it] | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | assets = | equity = | num_employees = | intl = | parent = | owner = [[Sky Italia]] }}
'''Mediaset Premium''' is an [[Italy|Italian]] [[digital terrestrial television]] service provided by [[Sky Italia]]. It provides [[Pay television|pay TV]] and [[pay-per-view]] (only for football matches) through the use of a [[smart card]] as well as [[video on demand]] through its Premium Play and Premium Online streaming service.
==History== [[File:Premium Cinema.svg|alt=|thumb|Premium Cinema logo]] Mediaset Premium was launched on January 20, 2005, initially offering only pay-per-view services for movies and sports.
In January 2008, it became a full pay TV, launching the package "Premium Gallery", available, with a package for football matches, through monthly subscription or prepaid. Over time, new packages and new channels enrich the offered.
In 2015, the new offering provides channels of movies, TV series, sport, documentaries, cartoons and interactive services ''Premium Play'' and ''Premium Online''. From 2016, Premium will also broadcast on satellite TV.
Broadcast until 2018 the [[UEFA Champions League]] exclusive in Italy on channels Premium Sports and Premium Calcio also in HD. It also owns the sports rights, in addition to the [[Serie A]], of foreign tournaments as the [[Ligue 1]] and the [[Coupe de France]], the [[Scottish Premiership]], also of the [[National Football League|NFL]] of [[American football]]. There are also channels [[Eurosport]] and [[Eurosport 2]].
In 2016 [[Vivendi]] agreed to buy 100% stake of Mediaset Premium and 3.5% stake of [[Mediaset]] by selling 3.5% stake of Vivendi's shares.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vivendi.com/en/press/press-releases/vivendi-forms-a-strategic-and-industrial-partnership-with-mediaset/|title=Vivendi forms a strategic and industrial partnership with Mediaset|date=8 April 2016|access-date=6 September 2016|publisher=Vivendi}}</ref> However, after inspecting the financial statements as well as income forecast, Vivendi did not wish to enforce the original terms but submitting a revised offer to buy 20% stake in Mediaset Premium, as well as buying convertible bonds of Mediaset Premium.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vivendi.com/en/press/press-releases/vivendi-and-mediaset-structure-of-the-offer/|title=Vivendi and Mediaset: structure of the offer|date=26 July 2016|access-date=6 September 2016|publisher=Vivendi}}</ref> [[Fininvest]], the majority owner of Mediaset, had choose to start legal action to Vivendi.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fininvest.it/assets/press/en/CS%20ENG%20Fininvest_Vivendi_23.8.16.pdf|title=Fininvest claims 570 million euros damages from Vivendi|date=23 August 2016|access-date=6 September 2016|publisher=Fininvest}}</ref>
